<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto pb-16">
  <nav role="breadcrumb" class="mb-6">
    <ul class="flex items-center space-x-3">
      <li>
        <%= link_to "Changelog", rui_changelog_path, class: "text-sm font-medium underline underline-offset-2" %>
      </li>
      <span class="opacity-50">/</span>
      <li>
        <%= link_to "Fixed rendering issue", "#" %>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <div class="bg-orange-500/10 text-orange-600 inline-block text-xs rounded px-1 py-0.5 font-medium dark:bg-orange-500/25 dark:text-orange-300">Bugfix</div>

  <div class="prose prose-gray dark:prose-invert mt-4 prose-headings:tracking-tight">
    <h1>Resolving Rendering Issues for a Better User Experience</h1>
    <div class="not-prose mb-6">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-start border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-700/80 gap-4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <%= image_tag demo_avatar_url(variant: "men", id: "36"), alt: "John Doe", class: "size-8 rounded-full" %>
          <p class="font-medium text-sm">John Doe</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <time class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400" datetime="">May 24, 2024</time>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>We are thrilled to announce a recent change to our codebase that brings significant improvements to the user experience! Our team has been hard at work addressing and fixing a rendering issue that was impacting certain devices.</p>

    <h2>The problem</h2>
    <p>Some users reported an issue with incorrect rendering on specific devices. This bug was causing frustration and hindering the seamless experience we strive to provide.</p>

    <h2>The solution</h2>
    <p>After thorough investigation and collaboration, our development team successfully identified and resolved the root cause of the rendering issue. We implemented a robust solution to ensure consistent and accurate rendering across all devices, delivering a smoother and more reliable user experience.</p>

    <h2>What's changed</h2>
    <p>We have deployed the necessary updates to our codebase to address this bug. Our commitment to quality and user satisfaction drove us to swiftly implement these changes, ensuring that our platform remains reliable and user-friendly.</p>

    <h2>How it benefits you</h2>
    <p>With this rendering issue resolved, our users can now enjoy a more seamless and visually consistent experience on their devices. Whether you're accessing our platform from a desktop, tablet, or mobile device, you can trust that the content will be displayed accurately, enhancing overall usability and satisfaction.</p>

    <h2>Next steps</h2>
    <p>We will continue to monitor the performance of these changes and remain vigilant for any potential issues. Your feedback is invaluable to us, so please don't hesitate to share your thoughts or report any anomalies you may encounter. Our team is dedicated to continuously improving our platform and ensuring it meets the highest standards of quality.</p>

    <p>Thank you for your patience and understanding as we work to enhance your experience on our platform. We look forward to delivering more exciting updates in the future!</p>

    <p>The Retriever team</p>
  </div>
</div>
